The paper discusses the efficacy of learning neural networks with neural networks, which is a topic closely related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. The focus on two-layer neural networks with a linear activation on the output node suggests that the paper may fall under the category of deep learning (cs.LG). The use of gradient descent method also suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE). The study of convergence to global minima and sample complexity may also suggest the sub-category of optimization (cs.SY). Finally, the mention of electron proton dynamics in the title may suggest a potential application in computer vision (cs.CV).
